<summary>
The paper explores the field of text-to-image generation, focusing on enhancing the visual quality of images produced by these models. It discusses a method of fine-tuning pre-trained models using a small, carefully selected set of high-quality images to significantly improve the aesthetic appeal of the generated images. This approach maintains the model's ability to generate a wide range of visual concepts while enhancing visual appeal. The method is shown to be effective across various model architectures, including diffusion and transformer-based models.
</summary>
